lines.text: tomorrow's taking me away from you
before i go down this broken road i follow
a thorn from a dying rose
the saddest scent of you will cling to me
then i'll turn around and run
if i stay with you and linger here
i will fade into the scenery
i've got nothing left to offer you
it's not that i don't care
all i ask is that you think of me
then i'll turn around and run
i hate to see you cry
then i'll turn around and run

paragraphs.text: tomorrow's taking me away from you like a jealous lover kiss me one last time before i go down this broken road i follow you will leave me torn and sting me like a thorn from a dying rose the saddest scent of you will cling to me i know
i will run to you when my journey's over wait for me keep our love alive i will dream of you till i reach the sun then i'll turn around and run to you
